    <h3 id="tools">Tools</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <h4 id="android-vulnerablity-analysis">Android Vulnerablity Analysis</h4>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/linkedin/qark/" target="_blank">qark : A tool to look for several security related Android application vulnerabilities</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/AndroBugs/AndroBugs_Framework" target="_blank">AndroBugs : An Android vulnerability analysis system</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/mwrlabs/drozer" target="_blank">Drozer : Security testing framework for Android</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="http://findbugs.sourceforge.net/" target="_blank">FindBugs : A program which uses static analysis to look for bugs in Java code</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/dpnishant/appmon" target="_blank">AppMon : An automated framework for monitoring and tampering system API calls of native apps on macOS, iOS and Android</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/antitree/manitree" target="_blank">manitree : AndroidManifest.xml security auditor</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/hahwul/droid-hunter" target="_blank">DROID-HUNTER : Android application vulnerability analysis and Android pentest tool</a></p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h4 id="reverse-engineering">Reverse Engineering</h4>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://ibotpeaches.github.io/Apktool/" target="_blank">Apktool : A tool for reverse engineering 3rd party, closed, binary Android apps</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/androguard/androguard" target="_blank">Androguard : A full python tool to play with Android files</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/pxb1988/dex2jar" target="_blank">dex2jar : Tool to work with android .dex and java .class files</a></p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h4 id="vms-for-testing">VMs for testing</h4>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/sh4hin/Androl4b" target="_blank">AndroL4b : An android security virtual machine based on ubuntu-mate</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://androidtamer.com/" target="_blank">Android Tamer : A Virtual / Live Platform for Android Professionals</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/mobisec/" target="_blank">MobiSec : Mobile security testing live environment</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://santoku-linux.com/" target="_blank">Santoku : Dedicated to mobile forensics, analysis, and security, and packaged in an easy to use, Open Source platform</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/oguzhantopgul/Vezir-Project" target="_blank">Vezir-Project : Yet Another Linux Virtual Machine for Mobile Application Pentesting and Mobile Malware Analysis</a></p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h4 id="mitm-test">MiTM Test</h4>

        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/google/nogotofail" target="_blank">nogotofail : A network security testing tool designed to help developers and security researchers spot and fix weak TLS/SSL connections</a></li>
